1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,500
Welcome to Everyones Video.

2
00:00:03,500 --> 00:00:07,200
This is the fastest way to add subtitles to any video.

3
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:12,800
We support six ASR engines from completely free to enterprise-grade.

4
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:17,500
The secret is our subtitle-first strategy. Most YouTube videos already have captions.

5
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:22,000
We grab those first. Only if they're missing do we call an ASR engine.

6
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:28,500
For Chinese content, FunASR from Alibaba DAMO Academy is free and nearly as good as paid APIs.

7
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:35,000
Once you have your SRT file, translate it to any language with a single command.

8
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:41,200
Then burn the subtitles right into the video. One script does it all.

9
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:46,000
Let's get started. Clone the repo and run setup.sh.

10
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:50,500
Your first subtitled video is five minutes away.
